## Best Practices

### Chart Titles

Always provide descriptive titles:

✅ **Good:** `title="Monthly Revenue 2026"`

❌ **Bad:** `title="Chart"`

### Color Schemes

Use appropriate color schemes:

- `cool` - Professional, calm data
- `warm` - Energy, activity
- `pastel` - Soft, approachable
- `vibrant` - Bold, attention-grabbing

### Legend Usage

Use legends when data needs context:

:::chart
:::chart-line {title="User Growth" legend=true}
Free Users: 1000
Free Users: 1500
Paid Users: 200
Paid Users: 350
:::
:::

### Grid Display

Add grids for easier reading:

:::chart
:::chart-bar {title="Performance Metrics" grid=true}
Metric A: 85
Metric B: 92
Metric C: 78
:::
:::

